# Introduction
This a guide on how to approach learning mu.  
If you follow this, you will be a mu master in no time at all!  
For any mu-specific technical questions, check out the [mu wiki](https://github.com/stelligent/mu/wiki).

# The Path to Becoming a mu Master

## [AWS CloudFormation (cfn)](http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/Welcome.html)
Get a basic idea of what AWS CloudFormation does by watching the [3 minute long introductory video](https://aws.amazon.com/cloudformation/).  
Go through the official AWS CloudFormation '[Getting Started guide](http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/GettingStarted.html).

Do you understand:
- [ ] What a cfn template does?
- [ ] How to declare resources and their properties within a cfn template?

Are you able to:
- [ ] Create a cfn stack
- [ ] Monitor a cfn stack's progress by viewing the 'Events'
- [ ] Update a cfn stack
- [ ] Delete a cfn stack

## mu

1. Listen to the [mu podcast](https://stelligent.com/2017/07/20/devops-on-aws-radio-mu-devops-on-aws-tool-episode-10/)  
Can you answer these questions from the podcast:
- [ ] What is mu and what problem does it solve? What are its benefits?
- [ ] How does someone use mu (including prereqs)?
- [ ] What types of programming languages and platforms are supported?
- [ ] What types of AWS architectures does mu support (i.e. traditional EC2, ECS, Serverless, etc.)?
- [ ] Which AWS services are provisioned by mu?
- [ ] Does mu support non-AWS implementations?
- [ ] What does mu install on my AWS account?

2. Watch the [mu video example](https://stelligent.com/2017/07/28/screencast-full-stack-devops-on-aws-tool/)

